# LoggerLog Test Fixture: Syslog Format (RFC 3164 / RFC 5424)

# RFC 3164 style (BSD syslog)
Jan 15 10:00:00 hostname sshd[1234]: Accepted publickey for root from 192.168.1.100 port 22 ssh2
Jan 15 10:00:05 hostname CRON[5678]: (root) CMD (cd / && run-parts --report /etc/cron.hourly)
Jan 15 10:00:10 hostname kernel: [12345.678901] TCP: request_sock_TCP: Possible SYN flooding on port 80. Sending cookies.
Jan 15 10:00:15 hostname systemd[1]: Started Session 42 of user admin.
Jan 15 10:00:20 hostname sudo:   admin : TTY=pts/0 ; PWD=/home/admin ; USER=root ; COMMAND=/usr/bin/systemctl restart nginx

